Vue.js
Vue.js is a progressive JavaScript framework for building user interfaces.
Basic Component
&lt;template&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;{{ title }}&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;button @click=&quot;increment&quot;&gt;Count: {{ count }}&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/template&gt;

&lt;script&gt;
export default {
  data() {
    return {
      title: &#039;Hello Vue&#039;,
      count: 0
    }
  },
  methods: {
    increment() {
      this.count++
    }
  }
}
&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;style scoped&gt;
button {
  padding: 8px 16px;
  background: #42b883;
  color: white;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
}
&lt;/style&gt;
Composition API
&lt;script setup&gt;
import { ref, computed } from &#039;vue&#039;

const count = ref(0)
const doubled = computed(() =&gt; count.value * 2)

function increment() {
  count.value++
}
&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;template&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Count: {{ count }}&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Doubled: {{ doubled }}&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;button @click=&quot;increment&quot;&gt;Increment&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/template&gt;
Key Features

Reactive data binding
Component-based architecture
Single-file components
Virtual DOM
Composition API
Easy to learn

When to Use

Progressive enhancement
Single-page applications
Interactive UIs
Rapid prototyping

devops/infrastructure/terraform.content:
Terraform
Terraform is an infrastructure as code tool for building, changing, and versioning infrastructure.
Overview
Terraform uses declarative configuration files to manage infrastructure across multiple cloud providers.
Basic Configuration
# main.tf
terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = &quot;hashicorp/aws&quot;
      version = &quot;~&gt; 5.0&quot;
    }
  }
}

provider &quot;aws&quot; {
  region = &quot;us-east-1&quot;
}

resource &quot;aws_instance&quot; &quot;web&quot; {
  ami           = &quot;ami-0c55b159cbfafe1f0&quot;
  instance_type = &quot;t2.micro&quot;

  tags = {
    Name = &quot;WebServer&quot;
  }
}
Common Commands
# Initialize
terraform init

# Plan changes
terraform plan

# Apply changes
terraform apply

# Destroy infrastructure
terraform destroy

# Format code
terraform fmt

# Validate configuration
terraform validate
Variables
# variables.tf
variable &quot;instance_type&quot; {
  description = &quot;EC2 instance type&quot;
  type        = string
  default     = &quot;t2.micro&quot;
}

# Use variable
resource &quot;aws_instance&quot; &quot;web&quot; {
  instance_type = var.instance_type
}
Best Practices

Use remote state storage
Organize with modules
Use workspaces for environments
Version control everything
Use variables for flexibility
Implement state locking
